&lt;p&gt;#LI-remote&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About Us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Circle is building the world‚Äôs leading all-in-one platform for online communities. We make it possible for creators, coaches, educators, and businesses to bring together their audience with engaging discussions, live streams, events, chat, courses, and payments ‚Äî all in one place, all under their own brand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We‚Äôre proud to be a fully remote company of around 180 (and growing!) team members from 30+ countries around the world. We seek exceptional individuals around the world, set them up to do the best work of their lives, and in turn, create a meaningful impact in their own lives. We don&#39;t track hours, but we do manage for high expectations very closely. We collaborate across time zones, are highly async, and like to document a lot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Twice a year, we bring the whole company together in beautiful places around the world for our company offsites. So far, we‚Äôve hosted offsites in Turkey, Portugal, Mexico, Thailand, Colombia, Italy, Ireland, and more, with still more to come!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We‚Äôre on the hunt for a &lt;strong data-start=&quot;211&quot; data-end=&quot;235&quot;&gt;Senior Legal Counsel&lt;/strong&gt; to become Circle‚Äôs very first in-house legal hire. If you love moving fast and giving clear, practical advice that helps teams get things done‚Äîthis could be your spot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the first 3-6 months, this role will focus mostly on commercial law, especially helping out with sales and contract renewals. Down the line, there will be room to grow into areas like&amp;nbsp;privacy (think CCPA and GDPR), product, and security compliance (SOC 2).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Circle is an incredibly fast-growing company ‚Äîwe‚Äôre adding new markets, building new products, and scaling a global team. You‚Äôll have a front-row seat to all of it, and your work will be a key part of what keeps us moving forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage the full contract lifecycle ‚Äî draft, review, and maintain foundational commercial documents for our products and services, such as terms of use, product and support policies, and customer contracts and disclosures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key point of contact to the Sales, Customer Success, and Customer Support teams for questions arising during the RFP stage, contract negotiation and renewals, customer onboarding, or other changes in the product releases and GTM function that may have implications for the way we interact with our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help evaluate and implement a contract lifecycle management tool (e.g. Ironclad) to streamline legal operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build scalable and effective legal processes and resources, including delivering training, developing guides/playbooks, and creating new templates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help Circle take on new challenges and business initiatives in a thoughtful, compliant, and efficient way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Circle‚Äôs privacy program compliance, including maintaining GDPR compliance, and improve the effectiveness of critical privacy compliance processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date on relevant regulations, standards, and best practices, and help adapt Circle‚Äôs governance, risk, and compliance (GRC) program accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll need to be successful&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 4-6 years of relevant legal experience, including time spent in-house at startup or growth-stage company, ideally in the tech/SaaS space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong work ethic and team-player mindset, with a willingness to do the job that needs to be done at any given time and adapt as business priorities change and new challenges emerge.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment with a high level of autonomy and accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills (both written and oral) and the ability to explain complex ideas in a succinct and digestible manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JD from an accredited law school and admission to the bar in the relevant jurisdiction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong alignment with our values. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.notion.so/Circle-Careers-223a15ea312c4922b793593d07add7fe?pvs=21&quot;&gt;Find our values on our career page&lt;/a&gt; if you haven‚Äôt read up on them yet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proficient in English (spoken, written, and reading) at a &lt;a href=&quot;https://magoosh.com/english-speaking/english-proficiency-levels-a-guide-to-determining-your-level/&quot;&gt;CEFR Level C2&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.govtilr.org/&quot;&gt;ILR Level 5&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Bonus points&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have extensive knowledge of GRC best practices for SaaS organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You‚Äôve helped a SaaS product achieve compliance with one or more security standards before (i.e. SOC 2 or ISO 27001).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
